abstract:
Geography distribution of sharks being generally very broad, one of the conditions required for their stratigraphic usefulness is fulfilled; another condition, i. e., short longevity, varies widely. This paper discusses :
— identification; dental variation depending on position in the mouth; dental anatomy; ontogenical variation; abnormalities;
— geographical distribution and factors that control it (currents, temperature, depth and distance from the coast, paleogeographic factors) ;
-—• longevity and evolution.
Some conclusions are presented
